Intuition
In a normal next greater element problem an element only needs to consider elements on its right but in a circular array elements near end must also consider elements at beginning as possible next greater elements before processing the element from left to right i preload the stack with beginning of the array , this stimulates wrapping around by placing the beginning of array into stack before the main traversal starts.

As a result when we process the last few elements the stack already contains the elements they would encounter after wrapping around, allowing us to reuse the standard monotonic stack approach.

Complexity
Time complexity:
O(n)

Space complexity:
O(n)

Code
class Solution:
    def nextGreaterElements(self, nums: List[int]) -> List[int]:
        n = len(nums)
        stack =[]
        result = [-1] * n
        for i in range(n-2,-1,-1):
            stack.append(nums[i])
        for i in range(n-1,-1,-1):
            curr = nums[i]
            while stack and stack[-1] <= curr:
                stack.pop()
            if stack:
                result[i] = stack[-1]
            stack.append(curr)
        return result
